Merge Craigslist main table with Reference tables for normalization 12


1.      Click on PackageLoadCraigsListODS.dtsx Package

 

a.      Drag and drop Data Flow Task on the canvas and rename Data Flow Task-LoadCraigsListODStemp

b.      Drag and drop Data Flow Task on the canvas and rename Data Flow Task-LoadCraigsListODSfinal.  Drop the precedence constraint from the top Data Flow Task to it

c.      Double click on Data Flow Task-LoadCraigsListODStemp to get to the Data Flow design canvas

 

d.      Drag and drop OLE DB source and destination transformations onto the canvas and drop precedence constraint from source to destination.  Rename them as OLE DB Source-STGfinal and OLE DB Destination-CraigsListODS Respectively

e.      Double click on source to configure as in below screenshot providing (1) the connection manager and the source table, and (2) selecting columns and their properties:

 

 


f.      Double click on the destination to configure as in screenshot below by providing (1) the connection manager and the destination table, and (2) mapping the source columns to the columns in the destination table:

  


2.      Double click on Data Flow Task-LoadCraigsListODSfinal to get to the Data Flow design canvas:

 



a.      Drag and drop OLE DB source transformations onto the canvas for the following source tables:

·        dbo.CraigsListODS and rename  the object as “OLE DB Source-CraigsODS”

·        dbo.Model and rename  the object as “OLE DB Source-Model”

·        dbo.Region and rename  the object as “OLE DB Source-Region”

·        dbo.PaintColor and rename  the object as “OLE DB Source-Color”

·        dbo.VehicleType and rename  the object as “OLE DB Source-VehicleType”

      

b.      Drag and drop the OLE DB destination onto the canvas and rename the object as OLE DB Destination-CraigsListODSfinal


c.      Drop 8 Sort transformations onto the canvas


d.      Drop precedence constraints from “OLE DB Source-CraigsODS” to a Sort Transformation.  Do similarly from “OLE DB Source-Model”.


e.      Double click on “OLE DB Source-CraigsODS “ to configure as in below screenshot providing (1) the connection manager and the source table, and (2) selecting columns and their properties:



f.      Double click on one of the Sort Transformation to configure as in below screenshot to sort the source table as per columns you want to sort on in the Model table specified in the “OLE DB Source-Model” source to be merged using Merge Transformation.  Indicate the columns you want to output into the destination table as Pas Through.



g.      Double click on “OLE DB Source-Model” to configure as in below screenshot providing (1) the connection manager and the source table, and (2) selecting columns and their properties:

 


h.      Double click on one of the Sort Transformation to configure as in below screenshot to sort the source table as per columns you want to sort on in the table specified in the “OLE DB Source-CraigsODS” source to be merged using Merge Transformation.  Indicate the columns you want merged into the destination table as Pas Through. In our case, it’s the IDs for Model and Manufacturer.

 


i.      Drag and drop Merge Join Transformation onto the canvas.  Drop the precedence constraints from the two configured Sort Transformations to the Merge Join Transformation. State the join type which is INNER JOIN.  Indicate the join key (columns) on either side – Model and Manufacturer names.  Indicate the columns to be merged from the Reference table.  In our case, it’s the IDs from the Model table – ModelID and ManufacturerID.  See below screenshot:



3.      Repeat the same for the rest of the Source files merging with the successive output of the table defined in “OLE DB Source-CraigsODS” after extracting the respective IDs.


4.      After the last Merge Join Transformation the resulting output is inserted into the destination table as below:

         Drag and drop OLE DB destination onto the canvas and double click it to configure as below screenshot:
